What makes you feel most at home? “Home is a feeling. What better feeling to have than being accepted & valued by the people closest to us?”

Like this post & we’ll donate. We’re obsessed with this young activist’s bedroom makeover and Q&A. 😍 @genesisbutler_ is an advocate for animal rights, and one of the youngest people to ever give a TEDx talk (#nbd). An ethical vegan since she was 6—she started @genesisforanimals, which provides funding to sanctuaries and rescues that provide animals with a permanent home. For each like this post gets, we will donate $3 toward Genesis’ causes (full donation amount up to $1500). Funding will go towards the care of animals including food, shelter, transportation costs, surgeries, and vet visits. Charity contact information: genesisforanimals@yahoo.org. Runs from 4/23 - 4/30.

Summer camp is alive & well in @ispydiy’s historic Milwaukee, WI #BayViewBarnHouse. ⛺ The mom and expert DIYer recently transformed her attic space into a camp-themed playroom. Tap through to shop the @crateandkids items featured, like our Plush Campfire Set, Wooden Toy Workbench and handy Gallery Wall Clips.

“The hardware store only had this paneling in stock, and once we installed it the room really felt like a Wisconsin cabin. There’s also the big pipe running along the roof…so I decided to lean into it and go with a vintage camp theme. It ended up being perfect because our girl is so adventurous, and our family loves hiking and being outdoors. I knew I wanted to include the Grey Bean Bag Chair from the beginning, because I needed a comfy spot to sit in the room while our girl plays. I quickly fell down the rabbit hole of all the campy kids decor at @crateandkids. I love that all the pieces (like the bookshelf, rug and basket) all fit in seamlessly with my thrifted items.”

Have you made over your attic into a kid space?
